";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"WPTavern: WPWeekly Episode 216 ‚Äì WordCamp US 2015 Recap Roundtable";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"http://wptavern.com?p=49524&preview_id=49524";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://wptavern.com/wpweekly-episode-216-wordcamp-us-2015-recap-roundtable";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2569:"<p>In this episode of WordPress Weekly, <a href="http://marcuscouch.com/">Marcus Couch</a> and I are joined by <a href="http://cantspeakgeek.com/">Michele Butcher</a>, <a href="http://cantspeakgeek.com/">Nikhil Vimil</a>, <a href="http://kikodoran.com/">Kiko Doran</a>, and <a href="https://www.chriswiegman.com/">Chris Wiegman</a> as we recap the first annual WordCamp US. We discuss the venue and share our favorite sessions of the event. We also discuss a number of items from Matt Mullenweg&#8217;s <a href="http://wordpress.tv/2015/12/07/matt-mullenweg-state-of-the-word-2015/">State of The Word</a> presentation. Last but not least are Marcus&#8217; plugin picks of the week.</p>
<h2>Stories Discussed:</h2>
<p><a href="http://wptavern.com/wordpress-4-4-clifford-featuring-responsive-images-twenty-sixteen-and-more">WordPress 4.4 ‚ÄúClifford‚Äù Featuring Responsive Images, Twenty Sixteen, and More<b> </b></a></p>
<h2>Plugins Picked By Marcus:</h2>
<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/popup-for-contact-form-7/">Popup for Contact Form 7</a> by Aiyaz Khorajia, from India, shows a popup when a form is submitted through Contact Form 7. You can customize the popup title, message, and colors from the backend.</p>
<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/reset-wp/">Reset WP</a> by Nikunj Soni, from India, resets the WP Database to a default installation. It resets only the database and does not modify or delete any files.</p>
<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/joan">Jock On Air Now</a> (aka JOAN) by G&amp;D Enterprises, in Brooklyn, NY, lets site admins manage and display a rotating programming schedule for radio or TV. Jock on air now(Joan) displays the name of the current show and the DJ or host in a given time-slot. It also displays the show/jock for the next time-slot. If nothing is scheduled, it displays a custom message.</p>
<h2>WPWeekly Meta:</h2>
<p><strong>Next Episode:</strong> Wednesday, December 16th 9:30 P.M. Eastern</p>
